    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here is a method I use to get the last nth characters of a string:</p>\n<pre><code>public static String takeLast(String value, int count) {\n    if (value == null || value.trim().length() == 0) return &quot;&quot;;\n    if (count &lt; 1) return &quot;&quot;;\n\n    if (value.length() &gt; count) {\n        return value.substring(value.length() - count);\n    } else {\n        return value;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Then use it like so:</p>\n<pre><code>String testStr = &quot;this is a test string&quot;;\nString last1 = takeLast(testStr, 1); //Output: g\nString last4 = takeLast(testStr, 4); //Output: ring\n</code></pre>\n"
